<h1>GeoAPIBD</h1>

<p>GeoAPIBD is a RESTful API developed with Go, designed to provide geographical information for Bangladesh, including divisions, districts, upazilas, and unions. This API allows users to retrieve data at various levels of granularity.</p>

<h2>Table of Contents</h2>
<ul>
  <li><a href="#features">Features</a></li>
  <li><a href="#endpoints">Endpoints</a></li>
  <li><a href="#setup">Setup</a></li>
  <li><a href="#environment-variables">Environment Variables</a></li>
  <li><a href="#usage">Usage</a></li>
  <li><a href="#license">License</a></li>
</ul>

<h2 id="features">Features</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Provides endpoints for retrieving data on divisions, districts, upazilas, and unions.</li>
  <li>Developed with <strong>Go</strong> and <strong>Echo</strong> framework for high performance and simplicity.</li>
  <li>Offers dynamic URL generation based on environment variables.</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="endpoints">Endpoints</h2>
<p>Below are the primary endpoints available in the API:</p>
<ul>
  <li><code>GET /api/divisions</code> - Retrieve all divisions.</li>
  <li><code>GET /api/districts</code> - Retrieve all districts.</li>
  <li><code>GET /api/division/{division_name}</code> - Retrieve a specific division by name.</li>
  <li><code>GET /api/division/{division_name}/districts</code> - Retrieve districts within a division.</li>
  <li><code>GET /api/division/{division_name}/upazilas</code> - Retrieve upazilas within a division.</li>
  <li><code>GET /api/division/{division_name}/district/{district_name}/upazilas</code> - Retrieve upazilas within a district.</li>
  <li><code>GET /api/division/{division_name}/district/{district_name}/upazila/{upazila_name}/unions</code> - Retrieve unions within an upazila.</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="setup">Setup</h2>
<p>To set up the project locally, follow these steps:</p>
<pre>
<code>
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/anik4good/bangladesh_geocode.git

# Change into the project directory
cd geoapibd

# Install dependencies
go mod tidy

# Run the application
go run main.go
</code>
</pre>

<h2 id="environment-variables">Environment Variables</h2>
<p>The application requires the following environment variables:</p>
<ul>
  <li><code>SERVER_URL</code>: The base URL for the API.</li>
</ul>
<p>Example:</p>
<pre>
<code>
export SERVER_URL=https://bdgeo.root2tech.com
</code>
</pre>

<h2 id="usage">Usage</h2>
<p>Once the server is running, you can use tools like <strong>curl</strong> or <strong>Postman</strong> to test the endpoints.</p>
<pre>
<code>
# Example request to get all divisions
curl https://bdgeo.root2tech.com/api/divisions
</code>
</pre>

